1
00:00:02,531 --> 00:00:04,161
Miles, fancy a drink?

2
00:00:04,203 --> 00:00:05,433
I can't.

3
00:00:05,473 --> 00:00:07,501
Keiko and the kids
are waiting on me for dinner.

4
00:00:07,544 --> 00:00:09,070
Next Thursday...
book a holosuite.

5
00:00:09,116 --> 00:00:10,278
They're going to Bajor.

6
00:00:12,089 --> 00:00:13,456
Hi, Julian.

7
00:00:13,494 --> 00:00:14,758
Hi.
You going to Vic's?

8
00:00:15,766 --> 00:00:16,735
Yes.

9
00:00:16,769 --> 00:00:18,637
Mind if I join you?

10
00:00:18,674 --> 00:00:21,512
Uh... actually, we
were looking forward

11
00:00:21,547 --> 00:00:23,677
to spending an evening alone.

12
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:25,350
Great.

13
00:00:25,391 --> 00:00:27,157
Well, have a great time.

14
00:00:29,234 --> 00:00:30,601
I understand.

15
00:00:41,432 --> 00:00:43,096
Cheeky virus.

16
00:00:43,137 --> 00:00:45,165
You've gone and mutated on me.

17
00:00:47,114 --> 00:00:50,520
Well, you can run,
but you can't hide.

18
00:00:58,544 --> 00:01:00,447
Lights.

19
00:01:02,922 --> 00:01:04,825
Nog to Dr. Bashir.

20
00:01:06,330 --> 00:01:07,856
Go ahead.

21
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:10,237
You're needed
in the Infirmary, sir.

22
00:01:10,274 --> 00:01:12,473
It's 3:00 in the morning.

23
00:01:12,513 --> 00:01:14,177
Isn't Dr. Girani on duty?

24
00:01:14,218 --> 00:01:16,486
Not anymore.

25
00:01:16,523 --> 00:01:18,426
Admiral Patrick threw her out.

26
00:01:19,665 --> 00:01:21,191
Admiral who?

27
00:01:21,236 --> 00:01:23,674
He wants to see you
immediately, sir.

28
00:01:23,709 --> 00:01:25,304
On my way.

29
00:01:32,264 --> 00:01:33,597
What's going on, Ensign?

30
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:35,002
Sir, Admiral Patrick
and his staff

31
00:01:35,038 --> 00:01:36,200
just arrived on the <i>Farragut.</i>

32
00:01:36,242 --> 00:01:37,506
What happened to Dr. Girani?

33
00:01:37,545 --> 00:01:38,946
The Admiral said
she was asking

34
00:01:38,982 --> 00:01:40,178
too many stupid questions.

35
00:01:44,998 --> 00:01:47,128
Dr. Bashir reporting as ordered.

36
00:01:47,169 --> 00:01:48,399
Finally.

37
00:01:49,442 --> 00:01:51,072
Patrick?!

38
00:01:51,113 --> 00:01:52,241
That's Admiral Patrick.

39
00:01:52,283 --> 00:01:54,254
Mind your manners, Doctor.

40
00:01:54,289 --> 00:01:55,383
What are you doing here?

41
00:01:55,491 --> 00:01:57,291
That's a stupid question.

42
00:01:57,329 --> 00:01:59,266
Where did you get
those uniforms?

43
00:01:59,302 --> 00:02:01,432
That's a stupid question, too.

44
00:02:01,473 --> 00:02:03,467
Please excuse the doctor, sir.

45
00:02:03,512 --> 00:02:04,606
He just woke up.

46
00:02:04,648 --> 00:02:06,744
They're not
Starfleet officers, Nog.

47
00:02:06,788 --> 00:02:07,950
They're not?

48
00:02:07,990 --> 00:02:09,016
We're mutants.

49
00:02:09,060 --> 00:02:11,328
Genetically engineered mutants.

50
00:02:11,366 --> 00:02:12,460
Can't you tell?

51
00:02:12,502 --> 00:02:14,872
Does anybody at the Institute
know you're missing?

52
00:02:14,909 --> 00:02:15,878
That's a stupid...

53
00:02:15,911 --> 00:02:17,939
Will you stop saying that!

54
00:02:17,983 --> 00:02:19,077
Why are you so upset?

55
00:02:19,119 --> 00:02:21,318
You wanted Sarina brought here.
Well...

56
00:02:22,729 --> 00:02:24,221
here she is.

57
00:02:26,405 --> 00:02:28,775
I was considering bringing
Sarina here for treatment

58
00:02:28,811 --> 00:02:30,041
when I was ready

59
00:02:30,081 --> 00:02:32,417
but I still have to modify
my surgical equipment

60
00:02:32,454 --> 00:02:34,084
before I can begin
the procedure.

61
00:02:34,125 --> 00:02:35,389
Well, don't worry...
we'll help you.

62
00:02:35,428 --> 00:02:36,795
And when we're
through with Sarina

63
00:02:36,832 --> 00:02:38,894
she will be just like us.

64
00:02:38,937 --> 00:02:40,703
Do you have any idea

65
00:02:40,742 --> 00:02:41,904
how much trouble
you could get into

66
00:02:41,945 --> 00:02:43,677
for impersonating
Starfleet officers?

67
00:02:43,717 --> 00:02:45,847
Jack, you didn't say anything
about us getting into trouble.

68
00:02:45,889 --> 00:02:47,051
Well, we didn't get caught,
did we?

69
00:02:47,092 --> 00:02:48,618
Didn't anybody question you?

70
00:02:48,662 --> 00:02:49,631
Of course.

71
00:02:49,665 --> 00:02:51,363
But when they did,
Patrick would say...

72
00:02:51,403 --> 00:02:53,033
That's a stupid...

73
00:02:53,074 --> 00:02:55,946
You'd be surprised
how well it works.

74
00:02:55,981 --> 00:02:57,280
I'll say.

75
00:02:57,318 --> 00:02:58,617
What are they going do to us?

76
00:02:58,655 --> 00:02:59,681
Oh, it's all right.

77
00:02:59,725 --> 00:03:01,058
I'll find a way

78
00:03:01,095 --> 00:03:04,001
to straighten this out...
somehow.

79
00:03:06,910 --> 00:03:08,277
Hello, Sarina.

80
00:03:08,314 --> 00:03:09,442
Remember me?

81
00:03:09,484 --> 00:03:11,455
Of course she remembers you.

82
00:03:11,555 --> 00:03:12,454
She's not an idiot.

83
00:03:12,558 --> 00:03:13,925
She's just a little cataleptic.

84
00:03:13,962 --> 00:03:15,592
Are you really
going to be able

85
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:16,693
to make her better?

86
00:03:16,735 --> 00:03:19,641
I'm going to do
everything I can.

87
00:03:19,676 --> 00:03:21,944
I promise.

88
00:05:19,590 --> 00:05:21,720
They posed as an Admiral
and his staff.

89
00:05:21,795 --> 00:05:23,857
If you want me to convince
Starfleet not to press charges

90
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:26,134
you're going to have to give me
a damn good reason.

91
00:05:26,173 --> 00:05:27,403
They wanted
to bring Sarina here

92
00:05:27,443 --> 00:05:28,503
so that I could help her.

93
00:05:28,546 --> 00:05:29,515
They meant well.

94
00:05:29,548 --> 00:05:30,517
They meant well?

95
00:05:30,551 --> 00:05:32,077
That's the same
excuse you gave me

96
00:05:32,122 --> 00:05:33,091
when they were caught

97
00:05:33,124 --> 00:05:35,220
trying to pass military
secrets to the Dominion.

98
00:05:35,264 --> 00:05:36,392
They were trying
to save lives...

99
00:05:36,433 --> 00:05:38,370
Doctor, I appreciate

100
00:05:38,405 --> 00:05:39,897
that you feel
a connection to them

101
00:05:39,942 --> 00:05:41,913
because you are genetically
engineered yourself

102
00:05:41,947 --> 00:05:43,211
but they have displayed

103
00:05:43,251 --> 00:05:45,279
a consistent disregard
for the rules

104
00:05:45,323 --> 00:05:46,987
that the rest of society
lives by.

105
00:05:47,027 --> 00:05:48,087
Maybe that's because

106
00:05:48,130 --> 00:05:50,260
they're not allowed
to live in society.

107
00:05:50,303 --> 00:05:52,206
We are not here
to debate Federation policy

108
00:05:52,241 --> 00:05:53,676
toward
the genetically enhanced.

109
00:05:53,711 --> 00:05:56,377
We are here to discuss
what to do about these people

110
00:05:56,418 --> 00:05:57,682
now that they're aboard.

111
00:05:57,721 --> 00:05:59,885
Of course.

112
00:05:59,928 --> 00:06:01,626
Well, with your permission, sir

113
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:04,434
I would like to proceed
with Sarina's treatment.

114
00:06:04,472 --> 00:06:05,771
Well, I take it the Institute

115
00:06:05,842 --> 00:06:07,676
has given the approval
to move forward?

116
00:06:07,714 --> 00:06:11,120
A copy of the medical
protocols I submitted.

117
00:06:11,157 --> 00:06:13,185
Dr. Loews,
Sarina's legal guardian

118
00:06:13,228 --> 00:06:14,492
has given her consent.

119
00:06:15,768 --> 00:06:17,500
Well, it appears
that this procedure

120
00:06:17,540 --> 00:06:18,804
has never been done before.

121
00:06:18,876 --> 00:06:20,813
Well, there's no guarantee
that it will work, of course

122
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:23,183
but if it does, it could change
everything for her.

123
00:06:23,221 --> 00:06:25,055
There's no reason
to think that she's suffering

124
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:27,064
from the same type
of behavioral disorders

125
00:06:27,098 --> 00:06:28,260
as Jack and the others.

126
00:06:28,301 --> 00:06:30,535
Her problem is that she's
trapped inside her own mind.

127
00:06:30,574 --> 00:06:32,204
This could free her.

128
00:06:32,245 --> 00:06:34,843
There are still a few technical
issues I have to work on

129
00:06:34,918 --> 00:06:37,584
but I feel confident
that I can iron them all out.

130
00:06:37,625 --> 00:06:41,294
You've put in a lot of time
on this, haven't you?

131
00:06:41,335 --> 00:06:42,770
I owe it to her, sir.

132
00:06:42,805 --> 00:06:45,141
I could have ended up
the same way as Sarina

133
00:06:45,178 --> 00:06:46,442
but I was lucky.

134
00:06:46,481 --> 00:06:47,745
My DNA re-sequencing

135
00:06:47,785 --> 00:06:49,984
didn't have
any unintended side effects.

136
00:06:51,996 --> 00:06:53,522
All right, Doctor.

137
00:06:53,567 --> 00:06:56,735
I'll take care of Starfleet.
You take care of Sarina.

138
00:06:56,775 --> 00:06:58,609
Thank you, sir.
I'll arrange to have

139
00:06:58,647 --> 00:07:00,777
the rest of the people
sent back to the Institute.

140
00:07:00,819 --> 00:07:02,311
Actually, I was hoping

141
00:07:02,356 --> 00:07:03,986
you'd allow them
to stay on for awhile.

142
00:07:04,027 --> 00:07:05,257
For what reason?

143
00:07:05,297 --> 00:07:07,268
Sarina's spent the last
15 years with them.

144
00:07:07,303 --> 00:07:09,001
Now, assuming
the procedure works

145
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,600
and she comes out
of her isolation

146
00:07:10,644 --> 00:07:12,342
I think it would be
helpful to have

147
00:07:12,382 --> 00:07:13,646
some familiar faces around.

148
00:07:13,686 --> 00:07:15,885
Well, we'll arrange
for quarters

149
00:07:15,924 --> 00:07:18,020
to be set up in the cargo bay.

150
00:07:18,064 --> 00:07:19,659
I appreciate it.

151
00:07:21,038 --> 00:07:23,237
Just make sure they stay there.

152
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:25,077
I don't want them to get
out and cause trouble

153
00:07:25,115 --> 00:07:26,414
like they did the last time.

154
00:07:26,452 --> 00:07:27,819
I'll see that it
doesn't happen again.

155
00:07:27,855 --> 00:07:29,154
I'll hold you to that.

156
00:07:29,193 --> 00:07:30,857
One thing more.

157
00:07:30,897 --> 00:07:32,629
Get them out
of those uniforms.

158
00:07:32,668 --> 00:07:33,659
Aye, sir.

159
00:07:36,077 --> 00:07:38,207
There.
Don't you look pretty?

160
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:39,445
Why are we doing this anyway?

161
00:07:39,486 --> 00:07:40,455
Keep going.

162
00:07:40,489 --> 00:07:41,685
Here?

163
00:07:41,725 --> 00:07:43,491
A little to the left.

164
00:07:45,267 --> 00:07:47,238
That's not where it was
last time.

165
00:07:47,272 --> 00:07:48,798
Oh, what difference
does it make?

166
00:07:48,844 --> 00:07:49,835
He's right.

167
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:50,974
Fine.

168
00:07:51,049 --> 00:07:52,143
How's that?

169
00:07:52,185 --> 00:07:53,176
Much better.

170
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:55,820
Here he is!

171
00:07:55,862 --> 00:07:57,492
Well, well, what did
the Captain say?

172
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:58,502
All systems are a go.

173
00:07:58,535 --> 00:07:59,663
See? See?

174
00:07:59,705 --> 00:08:01,642
I told you it was a good
idea to bring her here.

175
00:08:01,676 --> 00:08:02,940
That's right, Jack,
I remember.

176
00:08:02,981 --> 00:08:04,507
So, when do we operate?

177
00:08:04,551 --> 00:08:05,177
We?

178
00:08:06,222 --> 00:08:07,817
You're going to need some help.

179
00:08:07,859 --> 00:08:08,953
Oh, so you're a surgeon now?

180
00:08:09,062 --> 00:08:10,429
How hard can it be?

181
00:08:10,466 --> 00:08:11,901
Um, thanks for the offer, but...

182
00:08:11,937 --> 00:08:13,099
Oh, I get it.

183
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:14,609
You want to take
all the credit.

184
00:08:14,644 --> 00:08:15,613
It's not about credit.

185
00:08:15,647 --> 00:08:17,550
It's about what's best
for Sarina, I think.

186
00:08:17,585 --> 00:08:19,921
Fine. I'm busy, anyway.

187
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,450
New project.

188
00:08:21,495 --> 00:08:22,521
Oh, glad to hear it.

189
00:08:22,564 --> 00:08:23,658
What are you working on?

190
00:08:23,701 --> 00:08:25,501
Wouldn't you like to know?

191
00:08:26,541 --> 00:08:27,669
Well, I'll leave you to it

192
00:08:27,711 --> 00:08:28,737
but, uh, do me a favor

193
00:08:28,781 --> 00:08:30,581
and, uh, change out
of those uniforms.

194
00:08:37,904 --> 00:08:41,437
Sarina, I'd like to take
you to the Infirmary

195
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,915
and run a few tests.

196
00:08:42,950 --> 00:08:44,112
Is that all right?

197
00:08:45,591 --> 00:08:47,357
She's afraid it's going to hurt.

198
00:08:47,395 --> 00:08:49,559
It won't hurt.
I promise.

199
00:08:49,601 --> 00:08:51,299
You're in good hands...

200
00:08:51,339 --> 00:08:53,401
very good hands.

201
00:08:54,848 --> 00:08:55,874
Don't get your hopes up, Julian.

202
00:08:55,917 --> 00:08:58,481
It's over
between the two of us.

203
00:08:58,524 --> 00:09:00,586
I have a new man in my life...

204
00:09:00,630 --> 00:09:03,330
that gorgeous little Ferengi.

205
00:09:03,370 --> 00:09:04,600
Nog?

206
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,235
Jealous?

207
00:09:06,278 --> 00:09:08,716
Oh, that's so sweet.

208
00:09:12,895 --> 00:09:14,091
Hurry back.

209
00:09:20,347 --> 00:09:21,441
Sarina's cerebral cortex

210
00:09:21,484 --> 00:09:24,218
was genetically enhanced
in order to accelerate the rate

211
00:09:24,257 --> 00:09:26,285
at which
she can process information.

212
00:09:26,330 --> 00:09:29,361
Now, the only problem is,
her visual and auditory systems

213
00:09:29,405 --> 00:09:32,573
can't channel the stimuli
into the cortex fast enough

214
00:09:32,613 --> 00:09:34,014
so, because
they're out of sync

215
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:36,044
she can't focus on
what's going on around her.

216
00:09:36,088 --> 00:09:37,057
Well, is there any way

217
00:09:37,091 --> 00:09:38,789
to get her sensory
processors up to speed?

218
00:09:38,829 --> 00:09:39,798
I need to stimulate
the growth

219
00:09:39,831 --> 00:09:41,893
of new synapses in the thalamus

220
00:09:41,937 --> 00:09:45,470
which means...
I have to manipulate

221
00:09:45,513 --> 00:09:48,145
neural proteins
at a subatomic level.

222
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:50,157
Well, then you've
got a problem.

223
00:09:50,225 --> 00:09:53,165
This is the most advanced
neocortical probe made

224
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,103
and it's not nearly
that accurate.

225
00:09:55,138 --> 00:09:57,736
Now you know why
I asked you down here.

226
00:09:57,778 --> 00:09:59,008
Well, I wish I could
help you, Julian

227
00:09:59,048 --> 00:10:00,985
but at resolutions
that small

228
00:10:01,020 --> 00:10:04,324
quantum fluctuations
are impossible to control

229
00:10:04,361 --> 00:10:06,457
and I can't make this
thing any more accurate.

230
00:10:06,501 --> 00:10:09,030
How can you say that before
you've even tried it?

231
00:10:09,074 --> 00:10:11,569
I'm sorry, Julian.
It-it-it can't be done.

232
00:10:11,614 --> 00:10:12,810
I'm sorry.

233
00:10:12,850 --> 00:10:14,912
Well, sorry just isn't
good enough, Miles.

234
00:10:14,956 --> 00:10:18,397
This is Sarina's only chance
at living a normal life.

235
00:10:18,432 --> 00:10:21,166
Julian, I can't break
the laws of physics.

236
00:10:21,205 --> 00:10:22,299
Nobody can.

237
00:10:32,601 --> 00:10:34,435
Your friend was right.

238
00:10:34,473 --> 00:10:36,410
You can't break
the laws of physics.

239
00:10:38,851 --> 00:10:41,085
But you can bend them.

240
00:10:41,123 --> 00:10:43,391
We recalibrated
the imaging diodes.

241
00:10:43,429 --> 00:10:44,591
It is so accurate

242
00:10:44,632 --> 00:10:46,033
that you could clip
the wings of an angel

243
00:10:46,069 --> 00:10:47,402
dancing on the head of a pin.

244
00:10:47,439 --> 00:10:50,277
Uh... if you wanted to.

245
00:11:59,994 --> 00:12:02,090
Anything?

246
00:12:10,956 --> 00:12:12,790
Sarina?

247
00:12:12,894 --> 00:12:15,492
Now, just how am I
supposed to know

248
00:12:15,534 --> 00:12:17,060
you understand me

249
00:12:17,105 --> 00:12:21,138
if you don't give
me some sign, hmm?

250
00:12:21,182 --> 00:12:23,176
Anything.

251
00:12:23,221 --> 00:12:25,557
It doesn't matter how small.

252
00:12:37,158 --> 00:12:38,491
It's been five days now

253
00:12:38,528 --> 00:12:40,192
and she's just as unresponsive

254
00:12:40,231 --> 00:12:42,065
as she was before
the procedure.

255
00:12:42,103 --> 00:12:43,767
I know you're
disappointed, Julian

256
00:12:43,808 --> 00:12:45,711
but you did everything
that you could.

257
00:12:45,746 --> 00:12:47,444
Well, it wasn't enough.

258
00:12:48,821 --> 00:12:50,313
I'm sorry.

259
00:12:50,358 --> 00:12:53,230
Obviously, you want
to punish yourself.

260
00:12:53,265 --> 00:12:55,168
Do you want help?

261
00:12:55,204 --> 00:12:57,175
Because I'm really good
at punishing myself.

262
00:12:57,210 --> 00:12:58,543
Let's see...

263
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:01,348
if I were you,
I'd be kicking myself

264
00:13:01,386 --> 00:13:03,118
for making promises
I couldn't keep

265
00:13:03,158 --> 00:13:05,630
for getting people's hopes up

266
00:13:05,664 --> 00:13:07,133
for being arrogant
enough to think

267
00:13:07,168 --> 00:13:08,228
that I could help Sarina

268
00:13:08,271 --> 00:13:11,073
even though dozens
of other doctors have failed.

269
00:13:11,112 --> 00:13:12,081
Should I keep going?

270
00:13:12,114 --> 00:13:13,812
No.

271
00:13:13,852 --> 00:13:16,051
That just about covers it.
Thanks.

272
00:13:16,092 --> 00:13:17,618
Glad I could help.

273
00:13:20,403 --> 00:13:21,531
What is it?

274
00:13:24,113 --> 00:13:26,107
I'm not sure.

275
00:13:34,807 --> 00:13:35,969
Excuse me.

276
00:13:37,012 --> 00:13:38,481
Sarina?

277
00:13:38,517 --> 00:13:40,488
What are you looking at?

278
00:13:40,522 --> 00:13:43,792
Every... thing.

279
00:13:52,185 --> 00:13:55,421
You... heard me.

280
00:13:55,461 --> 00:13:58,731
I thought something

281
00:13:58,769 --> 00:14:01,367
and you heard it.

282
00:14:01,409 --> 00:14:02,901
Sarina...

283
00:14:04,049 --> 00:14:05,917
you spoke.

284
00:14:35,097 --> 00:14:36,692
Sarina.

285
00:14:36,735 --> 00:14:37,999
Come and sit down.

286
00:14:38,038 --> 00:14:40,272
I need to run a few tests.

287
00:14:47,929 --> 00:14:49,057
What is it?

288
00:14:49,133 --> 00:14:51,297
Listen.

289
00:14:52,442 --> 00:14:53,502
It's nice.

290
00:14:53,544 --> 00:14:54,535
You're right.

291
00:14:54,580 --> 00:14:56,072
I hadn't noticed that before.

292
00:14:57,922 --> 00:14:59,756
That's a little odd.

293
00:14:59,794 --> 00:15:03,463
Her norepinephrine levels
are slightly elevated.

294
00:15:03,503 --> 00:15:04,972
What's causing it?

295
00:15:05,008 --> 00:15:06,307
I'm not sure.

296
00:15:06,344 --> 00:15:10,286
It's probably due to
limbic overcompensation.

297
00:15:10,321 --> 00:15:11,951
The levels should drop

298
00:15:11,992 --> 00:15:13,963
when the new
thalamic connections

299
00:15:13,997 --> 00:15:15,523
stabilize.

300
00:15:15,569 --> 00:15:17,905
You're right... I think.

301
00:15:17,941 --> 00:15:19,707
I was listening

302
00:15:19,745 --> 00:15:23,848
when you were telling the
nurses about the procedure.

303
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:27,832
I kept thinking that
I wanted to thank you

304
00:15:27,867 --> 00:15:30,966
for what you were
trying to do for me...

305
00:15:31,008 --> 00:15:34,107
and now I finally can.

306
00:15:34,149 --> 00:15:36,120
Thank you.

307
00:15:42,204 --> 00:15:43,936
Did you move this?

308
00:15:43,975 --> 00:15:45,741
Maybe I did, maybe I didn't.

309
00:15:45,780 --> 00:15:48,309
Would you leave him alone?

310
00:15:48,353 --> 00:15:52,626
Patrick, it's where
it's supposed to be.

311
00:15:53,901 --> 00:15:55,427
Oh...

312
00:16:01,219 --> 00:16:03,885
Hello, everyone.

313
00:16:03,927 --> 00:16:06,126
Did you hear what she said?

314
00:16:06,199 --> 00:16:07,634
Did you hear that?

315
00:16:07,670 --> 00:16:09,071
I don't think I've heard

316
00:16:09,107 --> 00:16:10,941
a more beautiful
sound in my life.

317
00:16:10,979 --> 00:16:13,075
It was my idea
to bring you here!

318
00:16:13,118 --> 00:16:14,087
We missed you!

319
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:15,248
You look so different!

320
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:16,486
Aren't you going
to say thank you?

321
00:16:16,526 --> 00:16:17,552
Did the surgery hurt?

322
00:16:17,596 --> 00:16:21,436
There's so much I want
to say to all of you.

323
00:16:21,473 --> 00:16:23,273
Why are you talking
like that?

324
00:16:23,311 --> 00:16:24,678
Quiet!

325
00:16:24,714 --> 00:16:25,876
There's so much I want

326
00:16:25,917 --> 00:16:27,113
to say to all of you...
There's so much...

327
00:16:27,154 --> 00:16:28,123
Jack!

328
00:16:28,157 --> 00:16:30,128
No, he's right.

329
00:16:30,162 --> 00:16:31,826
I can hear the way I sound.

330
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:33,335
Don't worry.
It's only temporary.

331
00:16:33,370 --> 00:16:34,862
It just takes a little practice.

